            "title": "Old Testament Reading",
            "api_nlt_to_ref": "Chronicles.4:5-5:17",
            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3E1%20Chronicles%204%3A5-5%3A17%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_4_5%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-hanging%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EAshhur%20(the%20father%20of%20Tekoa)%20had%20two%20wives%2C%20named%20Helah%20and%20Naarah.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_4_6%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3ENaarah%20gave%20birth%20to%20Ahuzzam%2C%20Hepher%2C%20Temeni%2C%20and%20Haahashtari.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_4_7%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3EHelah%20gave%20birth%20to%20Zereth%2C%20Izhar%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E4%3A7%3C%2Fspan%3E%20As%20in%20an%20alternate%20reading%20in%20the%20Masoretic%20Text%20(see%20also%20Latin%20Vulgate)%3B%20the%20other%20alternate%20and%20the%20Greek%20version%20read%20%3Cem%3EZohar.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Ethnan%2C%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_4_8%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3Eand%20Koz%2C%20who%20became%20the%20ancestor%20of%20Anub%2C%20Zobebah%2C%20and%20all%20the%20families%20of%20Aharhel%20son%20of%20Harum.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_4_9%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-hanging%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3EThere%20was%20a%20man%20named%20Jabez%20who%20was%20more%20honorable%20than%20any%20of%20his%20brothers.%20His%20mother%20named%20him%20Jabez%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E4%3A9%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cem%3EJabez%3C%2Fem%3E%20sounds%20like%20a%20Hebrew%20word%20meaning%20%26%23x201C%3Bdistress%26%23x201D%3B%20or%20%26%23x201C%3Bpain.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%20because%20his%20birth%20had%20been%20so%20painful.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_4_10%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20was%20the%20one%20who%20prayed%20to%20the%20God%20of%20Israel%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BOh%2C%20that%20you%20would%20bless%20me%20and%20expand%20my%20territory!%20Please%20be%20with%20me%20in%20all%20that%20I%20do%2C%20and%20keep%20me%20from%20all%20trouble%20and%20pain!%26%23x201D%3B%20And%20God%20granted%20him%20his%20request.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_4_11%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-hanging%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3EKelub%20(the%20brother%20of%20Shuhah)%20was%20the%20father%20of%20Mehir.%20Mehir%20was%20the%20father%20of%20Eshton.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_4_12%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3EEshton%20was%20the%20father%20of%20Beth-rapha%2C%20Paseah%2C%20and%20Tehinnah.%20Tehinnah%20was%20the%20father%20of%20Ir-nahash.%20These%20were%20the%20descendants%20of%20Recah.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_4_13%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-hanging%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20sons%20of%20Kenaz%20were%20Othniel%20and%20Seraiah.%20Othniel%26%23x2019%3Bs%20sons%20were%20Hathath%20and%20Meonothai.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E4%3A13%3C%2Fspan%3E%20As%20in%20some%20Greek%20manuscripts%20and%20Latin%20Vulgate%3B%20Hebrew%20lacks%20%3Cem%3Eand%20Meonothai.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_4_14%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3EMeonothai%20was%20the%20father%20of%20Ophrah.%20Seraiah%20was%20the%20father%20of%20Joab%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20the%20Valley%20of%20Craftsmen%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E4%3A14%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Or%20%3Cem%3EJoab%2C%20the%20father%20of%20Ge-harashim.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20so%20called%20because%20they%20were%20craftsmen.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_4_15%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%2215%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-hanging%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E15%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20sons%20of%20Caleb%20son%20of%20Jephunneh%20were%20Iru%2C%20Elah%2C%20and%20Naam.%20The%20son%20of%20Elah%20was%20Kenaz.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_4_16%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%2216%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-hanging%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20sons%20of%20Jehallelel%20were%20Ziph%2C%20Ziphah%2C%20Tiria%2C%20and%20Asarel.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_4_17%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%2217%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-hanging%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E17%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20sons%20of%20Ezrah%20were%20Jether%2C%20Mered%2C%20Epher%2C%20and%20Jalon.%20One%20of%20Mered%26%23x2019%3Bs%20wives%20became%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E4%3A17%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Or%20%3Cem%3EJether%26%23x2019%3Bs%20wife%20became%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%20Hebrew%20reads%20%3Cem%3EShe%20became.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20the%20mother%20of%20Miriam%2C%20Shammai%2C%20and%20Ishbah%20(the%20father%20of%20Eshtemoa).%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_4_18%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%2218%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E18%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20married%20a%20woman%20from%20Judah%2C%20who%20became%20the%20mother%20of%20Jered%20(the%20father%20of%20Gedor)%2C%20Heber%20(the%20father%20of%20Soco)%2C%20and%20Jekuthiel%20(the%20father%20of%20Zanoah).%20Mered%20also%20married%20Bithia%2C%20a%20daughter%20of%20Pharaoh%2C%20and%20she%20bore%20him%20children.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_4_19%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%2219%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-hanging%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E19%3C%2Fspan%3EHodiah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20wife%20was%20the%20sister%20of%20Naham.%20One%20of%20her%20sons%20was%20the%20father%20of%20Keilah%20the%20Garmite%2C%20and%20another%20was%20the%20father%20of%20Eshtemoa%20the%20Maacathite.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_4_20%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%2220%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-hanging%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E20%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20sons%20of%20Shimon%20were%20Amnon%2C%20Rinnah%2C%20Ben-hanan%2C%20and%20Tilon.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-hanging%22%3EThe%20descendants%20of%20Ishi%20were%20Zoheth%20and%20Ben-zoheth.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_4_21%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%2221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EDescendants%20of%20Judah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Son%20Shelah%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-hanging-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E21%3C%2Fspan%3EShelah%20was%20one%20of%20Judah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20sons.%20The%20descendants%20of%20Shelah%20were%20Er%20(the%20father%20of%20Lecah)%3B%20Laadah%20(the%20father%20of%20Mareshah)%3B%20the%20families%20of%20linen%20workers%20at%20Beth-ashbea%3B%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_4_22%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%2222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E22%3C%2Fspan%3EJokim%3B%20the%20men%20of%20Cozeba%3B%20and%20Joash%20and%20Saraph%2C%20who%20ruled%20over%20Moab%20and%20Jashubi-lehem.%20These%20names%20all%20come%20from%20ancient%20records.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_4_23%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%2223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E23%3C%2Fspan%3EThey%20were%20the%20pottery%20makers%20who%20lived%20in%20Netaim%20and%20Gederah.%20They%20lived%20there%20and%20worked%20for%20the%20king.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_4_24%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%2224%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EDescendants%20of%20Simeon%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-hanging-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E24%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20sons%20of%20Simeon%20were%20Jemuel%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E4%3A24a%3C%2Fspan%3E%20As%20in%20Syriac%20version%20(see%20also%20Gen%2046%3A10%3B%20Exod%206%3A15)%3B%20Hebrew%20reads%20%3Cem%3ENemuel.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Jamin%2C%20Jarib%2C%20Zohar%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E4%3A24b%3C%2Fspan%3E%20As%20in%20parallel%20texts%20at%20Gen%2046%3A10%20and%20Exod%206%3A15%3B%20Hebrew%20reads%20%3Cem%3EZerah.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20and%20Shaul.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_4_25%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%2225%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-hanging%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E25%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20descendants%20of%20Shaul%20were%20Shallum%2C%20Mibsam%2C%20and%20Mishma.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_4_26%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%2226%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-hanging%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E26%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20descendants%20of%20Mishma%20were%20Hammuel%2C%20Zaccur%2C%20and%20Shimei.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_4_27%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%2227%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-hanging%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E27%3C%2Fspan%3EShimei%20had%20sixteen%20sons%20and%20six%20daughters%2C%20but%20none%20of%20his%20brothers%20had%20large%20families.%20So%20Simeon%26%23x2019%3Bs%20tribe%20never%20grew%20as%20large%20as%20the%20tribe%20of%20Judah.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_4_28%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%2228%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-hanging%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E28%3C%2Fspan%3EThey%20lived%20in%20Beersheba%2C%20Moladah%2C%20Hazar-shual%2C%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_4_29%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%2229%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E29%3C%2Fspan%3EBilhah%2C%20Ezem%2C%20Tolad%2C%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_4_30%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%2230%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E30%3C%2Fspan%3EBethuel%2C%20Hormah%2C%20Ziklag%2C%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_4_31%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%2231%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E31%3C%2Fspan%3EBeth-marcaboth%2C%20Hazar-susim%2C%20Beth-biri%2C%20and%20Shaaraim.%20These%20towns%20were%20under%20their%20control%20until%20the%20time%20of%20King%20David.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_4_32%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%2232%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E32%3C%2Fspan%3ETheir%20descendants%20also%20lived%20in%20Etam%2C%20Ain%2C%20Rimmon%2C%20Token%2C%20and%20Ashan%26%23x2014%3Bfive%20towns%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_4_33%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%2233%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E33%3C%2Fspan%3Eand%20their%20surrounding%20villages%20as%20far%20away%20as%20Baalath.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E4%3A33%3C%2Fspan%3E%20As%20in%20some%20Greek%20manuscripts%20(see%20also%20Josh%2019%3A8)%3B%20Hebrew%20reads%20%3Cem%3EBaal.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20This%20was%20their%20territory%2C%20and%20these%20names%20are%20listed%20in%20their%20genealogical%20records.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_4_34%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%2234%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-hanging%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E34%3C%2Fspan%3EOther%20descendants%20of%20Simeon%20included%20Meshobab%2C%20Jamlech%2C%20Joshah%20son%20of%20Amaziah%2C%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_4_35%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%2235%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E35%3C%2Fspan%3EJoel%2C%20Jehu%20son%20of%20Joshibiah%2C%20son%20of%20Seraiah%2C%20son%20of%20Asiel%2C%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_4_36%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%2236%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E36%3C%2Fspan%3EElioenai%2C%20Jaakobah%2C%20Jeshohaiah%2C%20Asaiah%2C%20Adiel%2C%20Jesimiel%2C%20Benaiah%2C%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_4_37%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%2237%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E37%3C%2Fspan%3Eand%20Ziza%20son%20of%20Shiphi%2C%20son%20of%20Allon%2C%20son%20of%20Jedaiah%2C%20son%20of%20Shimri%2C%20son%20of%20Shemaiah.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_4_38%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%2238%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-sp%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E38%3C%2Fspan%3EThese%20were%20the%20names%20of%20some%20of%20the%20leaders%20of%20Simeon%26%23x2019%3Bs%20wealthy%20clans.%20Their%20families%20grew%2C%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_4_39%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%2239%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E39%3C%2Fspan%3Eand%20they%20traveled%20to%20the%20region%20of%20Gerar%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E4%3A39%3C%2Fspan%3E%20As%20in%20Greek%20version%3B%20Hebrew%20reads%20%3Cem%3EGedor.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20in%20the%20east%20part%20of%20the%20valley%2C%20seeking%20pastureland%20for%20their%20flocks.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_4_40%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%2240%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E40%3C%2Fspan%3EThey%20found%20lush%20pastures%20there%2C%20and%20the%20land%20was%20spacious%2C%20quiet%2C%20and%20peaceful.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3ESome%20of%20Ham%26%23x2019%3Bs%20descendants%20had%20been%20living%20in%20that%20region.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_4_41%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%2241%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E41%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20during%20the%20reign%20of%20King%20Hezekiah%20of%20Judah%2C%20these%20leaders%20of%20Simeon%20invaded%20the%20region%20and%20completely%20destroyed%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E4%3A41%3C%2Fspan%3E%20The%20Hebrew%20term%20used%20here%20refers%20to%20the%20complete%20consecration%20of%20things%20or%20people%20to%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20either%20by%20destroying%20them%20or%20by%20giving%20them%20as%20an%20offering.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20the%20homes%20of%20the%20descendants%20of%20Ham%20and%20of%20the%20Meunites.%20No%20trace%20of%20them%20remains%20today.%20They%20killed%20everyone%20who%20lived%20there%20and%20took%20the%20land%20for%20themselves%2C%20because%20they%20wanted%20its%20good%20pastureland%20for%20their%20flocks.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_4_42%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%2242%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E42%3C%2Fspan%3EFive%20hundred%20of%20these%20invaders%20from%20the%20tribe%20of%20Simeon%20went%20to%20Mount%20Seir%2C%20led%20by%20Pelatiah%2C%20Neariah%2C%20Rephaiah%2C%20and%20Uzziel%26%23x2014%3Ball%20sons%20of%20Ishi.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr1_4_43%22%20bk%3D%22chr1%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%2243%22%3E%3C